io.confluent.ksql.test.util

Class ImmutableTester

  • java.lang.Object
    • io.confluent.ksql.test.util.ImmutableTester

  • public final class ImmutableTester
extends java.lang.Object
    Tests that a type is immutable.

    To be classed as immutable it must:

    • Annotated @Immutable
    • Each field, including static fields, must:
      • be final
      • be of a immutable type

    The tester knows about (most) JDK immutable types.

    Types from other libraries that are known to be immutable, but which are not annotated as such, can be registered with the tester as immutable, e.g. via withKnownImmutableType(java.lang.Class<?>).

    Where a field is not of an immutable type, but is known to be immutable by its usage patterns, it can be annotated with @EffectivelyImmutable.
